        <body>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-1" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <personGrp>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">Holy Community composed of the convents great and small around the city of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/8">Amida</placeName></persName>
                    </personGrp>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">405</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">607</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-2" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <date notBefore="0521" notAfter="0526" calendar="Gregorian">Between A.D. 521 and 526</date><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>was forced to leave<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">their monastery</placeName>by the defenders of the corrupt synod of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/622">Chalcedon</placeName>.<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">The community</persName>was so large, that the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2813">monastery of Mar Mama</placeName>in the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2796">village of Hzyn</placeName>in<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2858">Ṭyšf</placeName>could not hold them. 
                                
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/council-of-Chalcedon-451 http://syriaca.org/keyword/exile"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">406</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">608</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-3" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <date notBefore="0521" notAfter="0526" calendar="Gregorian">For five years</date><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>attracted many into their company, some coming as far as<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2798">Ingilene</placeName>. All were impressed by the religious devotion of<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>; all who joined them turned from sin, committing their lives to prayer, worship, singing, and monastic devotion.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/healing http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/sanctity http://syriaca.org/keyword/fasting http://syriaca.org/keyword/religion http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/tears http://syriaca.org/keyword/repentance http://syriaca.org/keyword/purity http://syriaca.org/keyword/matins http://syriaca.org/keyword/singing http://syriaca.org/keyword/vespers http://syriaca.org/keyword/hours http://syriaca.org/keyword/liturgy http://syriaca.org/keyword/stylites http://syriaca.org/keyword/demonology"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">412</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">614</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-4" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                           When<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>was at<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2813">Mar Mama</placeName>, a miracle occurred, where those affected by famine were fed by unending bread at the monastery after the fathers had prayed.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/miracles http://syriaca.org/keyword/fasting http://syriaca.org/keyword/prayer http://syriaca.org/keyword/bread http://syriaca.org/keyword/monastic-heads http://syriaca.org/keyword/poor http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">416</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">618</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-5" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <date when="0526" calendar="Gregorian">After five years</date>in<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2813">Mar Mara</placeName>,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>returned to<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2737">Amida</placeName>, but because of persecution, relocated to the border territory of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2774">the East</placeName>, near the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2785">hot springs</placeName>of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2751">Abarne</placeName>, settling at the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2834">convent of the Poplars</placeName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/travel http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution http://syriaca.org/keyword/monks"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">417</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">619</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-6" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                           <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">The community</persName>was too large for the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2834">convent of the Poplars</placeName>, so they constructed several buildings and homes.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/builders http://syriaca.org/keyword/architecture http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/architects"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">417</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">619</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-7" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2284">Justinian</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">417</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">619</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-8" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2284"/>
                        <occupation ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/kings">
                            <note type="desc">
                                <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2284">Justinian</persName>was king.
                            </note>
                        </occupation>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">417</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">619</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-9" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            At beginning of the reign of<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2284">Justinian</persName>,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>was allowed to return to their destroyed<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">monastery</placeName>. And<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">they</persName>began to restore their convents.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/exile http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/council-of-Chalcedon-451"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">418</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">620</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-10" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">The community</persName>was forced to leave a second time, this time to the<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2851">convent</placeName>of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2850">Thella d Thuthe in<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2783">Gumtha</placeName></placeName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/exile http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">418</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">620</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-11" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">The community</persName>was expelled from<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2851">the convent at<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2850">Thella d Thuthe</placeName></placeName>, so they returned to<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2834">the monastery of the Poplars</placeName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/exile http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">418</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">620</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-12" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2274">Ephraim the persecutor</persName>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">419</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">621</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-13" resp="#syoung">
                <listPerson>
                    <person>
                        <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2274"/>
                        <occupation ref="http://syriaca.org/keyword/patriarchs">
                            <note type="desc">
                                <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2274">Ephraim</persName>was patriarch of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/10">Antioch</placeName>
                            </note>
                        </occupation>
                    </person>
                </listPerson>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">419</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">621</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-14" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/2274">Ephraim</persName>began to persecute<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>, so that they were divided over the territories of<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2775">Edessa</placeName>,<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2839">Samosata</placeName>,<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2800">Izla</placeName>,<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2818">Melitene</placeName>,<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/94">Perrhe</placeName>,and <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/719">'Arab</placeName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution http://syriaca.org/keyword/exile http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries http://syriaca.org/keyword/suffering"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">419</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">621</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-15" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            After building many monasteries in exile,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>returned to their convents in<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2736">Amida</placeName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/exile http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution http://syriaca.org/keyword/builders http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasteries"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">420</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">622</citedRange>
                </bibl>
            </div>
            <div uri="http://syriaca.org/spear/827-16" resp="#syoung">
                <listEvent>
                    <event>
                        <desc>
                            For a third time,<persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/3506">the community</persName>was forced to leave<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/399">their convent</placeName>, travelling to<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/2800">Izla</placeName>,<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/719">'Arab</placeName>,and<placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/67">Dara</placeName>.
                        </desc>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/persecution http://syriaca.org/keyword/travel http://syriaca.org/keyword/exile http://syriaca.org/keyword/suffering http://syriaca.org/keyword/monasticism"/>
                    </event>
                </listEvent>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/work/827"/>
                    <citedRange unit="pp">421</citedRange>
                </bibl>
                <bibl type="primary">
                    <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2032"/>
